                        "ph": [
                            {
                                "@keyref": "prodname",
                                "#tail": "lets you easily search"
                            },
                            {
                                "@keyref": "companyfirst",
                                "#tail": "sources and related Web content."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "It's as easy as 1, 2, 3.",
                    {
                        "ph": {
                            "@keyref": "prodname",
                            "#tail": "analyzes them, and offers suggestions."
                        },
                        "#text": "As you enter search terms,"
                    },
                    "Search terms can include connectors (such as \"and\", \"or\", \"near\"). You can use the wildcard characters * (at the end of a root word) and ? (as any single character) to find variations of words.",
                    "For more information about using connectors or finding variations of words, please refer to those Help topics.",
                    {
                        "ph": [
                            {
                                "@keyref": "shepardizefirst",
                                "#tail": "a citation, select the"
                            },
                            {
                                "@keyref": "shepards",
                                "#tail": "tab, then enter your citation. You can also enter \"shep\", followed by a colon, followed by the document citation, for examlpe, shep: 800 f.2d 111."
                            }
                        ],
                        "#text": "To"
                    },
                    "You can use the links at the bottom of the search box to limit search results to specific:",
                    "Then select the Search button to run your search.",
                    "Any limitations you set remain in effect for subsequent searches.",
                    "You can use the Search Options form to enter or add to your search terms by selecting the \"Search Options\" link at the bottom of the search box. Use the drop-down list to select the relationships between terms, then enter the terms in the search field.",
                    "Select the \"Add to search\" button to add terms. When your search terms are complete, select the Close button to return to the search screen.",
                    "You can also run a search you saved to a work folder or from the search history. These are listed in the \"My Workspace\" area of the search form. Just select the search you want to run.",
